BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mealplan-20260511-breakfast-1@mealplanner
DTSTAMP:20260516T114413Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T080000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T090000
SUMMARY:🍳 Breakfast: Overnight Oats
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Overnight Oats\nServings: 2\nPrep: 5 min | Total: 5 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 1 cup rolled oats\n• 1 cup milk\n• 0.5 cup greek yogurt\n• 2 tbsp honey\n• 0.5 cup blueberries\n• 2 tbsp chia seeds\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Combine oats, milk, yogurt, honey, and chia seeds in a jar or container.\n2. Stir well, cover, and refrigerate overnight (or at least 4 hours).\n3. Top with blueberries before serving. Eat cold or microwave 1-2 min.\n\nTip: Swap blueberries for banana, strawberries, or any fruit. Add peanut butter for extra protein.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mealplan-20260511-lunch-2@mealplanner
DTSTAMP:20260516T114413Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T120000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T130000
SUMMARY:🥗 Lunch: Breakfast Burrito
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Breakfast Burrito\nServings: 2\nPrep: 5 min | Cook: 10 min | Total: 15 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 4 eggs\n• 2 large flour tortillas\n• 4 slice bacon\n• 0.5 cup shredded cheddar cheese\n• 0.25 cup salsa\n• 1 tbsp butter\n• 1 avocado\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Cook bacon in a skillet until crispy. Remove and chop.\n2. Whisk eggs, melt butter in the same skillet, and scramble eggs over medium heat.\n3. Warm tortillas in microwave for 15 seconds.\n4. Fill each tortilla with eggs, bacon, cheese, sliced avocado, and salsa.\n5. Fold and roll into burritos. Optional: toast seam-side down in a dry pan for 1 minute.\n\nTip: Meal prep: wrap in foil and freeze. Reheat in microwave 2-3 min.
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mealplan-20260511-dinner-3@mealplanner
DTSTAMP:20260516T114413Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T183000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260511T193000
SUMMARY:🍽️ Dinner: Spicy Sriracha Noodles
DESCRIPTION:Recipe: Spicy Sriracha Noodles\nServings: 2\nPrep: 5 min | Cook: 10 min | Total: 15 min\n\n--- Ingredients ---\n• 4.0 oz lo mein noodles\n• 2.0 tbsp vegan butter (Earth Balance)\n• 0.25 tsp crushed red pepper\n• 2.0 large eggs\n• 1.0 tbsp brown sugar\n• 1.0 tbsp soy sauce\n• 2.0 tbsp sriracha\n• 1.0 handful fresh cilantro\n• 1.0 green onion, sliced\n\n--- Steps ---\n1. Prepare the sauce for the noodles. In a small bowl, stir together the brown sugar, soy sauce, and sriracha. Set the sauce aside.\n2. Bring a pot of water to a boil for the noodles. Once boiling, add the noodles and boil until tender. Drain the noodles in a colander.\n3. While waiting for the water to boil, crack two eggs into a bowl then whisk lightly.\n4. Heat the butter in a skillet over medium heat, then add the eggs and crushed pepper and lightly scramble the eggs. Avoid over cooking the eggs.\n5. Once the noodles have drained, add them to the skillet with the eggs, then drizzle the sauce over top. Toss the noodles and eggs to coat in the sauce.\n6. Top the noodles with fresh cilantro and sliced green onion, then serve.\n\nTip: 🥛 DAIRY-FREE SWAPS: butter → vegan butter (Earth Balance). These sweet, tangy, and spicy sriracha noodles take only a few minutes to make and are an inexpensive alternative to take out.\n\nSource: https://www.budgetbytes.com/dragon-noodles/
IMAGE;VALUE=URI:https://www.budgetbytes.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Spicy-Noodles-skillet.jpg
URL:https://www.budgetbytes.com/dragon-noodles/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
END:VEVENT
